<h2>Costume Story</h2><p class="para-1">
On that day, the boy discovered his light anew.<br><br>
He faces the tragedy his own mistakes wrought
and the foolishness of the ideals he held.<br><br>
He knows the intentional, organized cruelty
of the societal structures humans establish.<br><br>
Consumed by despair, the boy lost his light.<br><br>
Many sneered at his dream, calling it unattainable.<br><br>
But no amount of ridicule could convince him to give
up on his dream, or saving those who need help.<br><br>
Rising to his feet, he flings open the door before him.<br><br>
"If conflict breeds conflict...
then surely dreams must breed dreams."<p>
